Many years ago I had one. I found him abandoned in a parking lot, starving, with tar and bubble gum stuck in his shaggy coat, and took him in. I cleaned him up and fed him and when he started to look a little less bedraggled and his ribs didn't stick out any more, I took him to a vet. I hope he had a good life.

Maine Coon cats are big and shaggy with coarse stiff fur, square jaws, lynx tufts on their ears--supposedly they carry some lynx genes, they are close enough genetically to interbreed--and tufts between their toes. They are almost mute, with tiny kittenish voices, and sometimes almost look and sound like they're straining to make a tiny squeaky mew. At the time I remember thinking that they looked like Neanderthal cats.

So a female Maine Coon cat would look like Cloris Leachman.
